HEADWORD: -ly
<hw>-ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>suff.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>-lich</ets>,
AS. <ets>-lic</ets>, orig. the same word as E. <ets>like</ets>, a. See
<er>Like</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>A suffix forming adjectives and
adverbs, and denoting <sig>likeness</sig> or <sig>resemblance</sig>;
<as>as, housewife<ex>ly</ex> duties</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> -ish(postnominal), -y(postnominal).</syn>⟦br⟧
